The Vice President, Mike Pence, spoke at an event on American energy, praising the Trump administration's commitment to unleashing the potential of America's energy resources. He highlighted President Trump's actions, such as approving the Keystone and Dakota pipelines, reopening coal mines, rolling back the Clean Power Plan, and withdrawing from the Paris Climate Accord. Pence emphasized the importance of affordable, abundant, and reliable energy as the foundation of American prosperity. He then introduced President Trump to speak at the event.